value.name: Limestone - Wikipedia
value.snippet: Limestone (calcium carbonate CaCO 3) is a type of carbonate sedimentary rock which is the main source of the material lime. It is composed mostly of the minerals calcite and aragonite, which are different crystal forms of CaCO 3. Limestone forms when these minerals precipitate out of water containing dissolved calcium.

value.name: Limestone | Characteristics, Formation, Texture, Uses, & Facts
value.snippet: limestone, sedimentary rock composed mainly of calcium carbonate (CaCO3), usually in the form of calcite or aragonite. It may contain considerable amounts of magnesium carbonate (dolomite) as well; minor constituents also commonly present include clay, iron carbonate, feldspar, pyrite, and quartz. Most limestones have a granular texture.

value.name: Limestone - Sedimentary rocks - Sandatlas
value.snippet: Limestone. Limestone is a very common sedimentary rock consisting of calcium carbonate (more than 50%). It is the most common non-siliciclastic ( sandstone and shale are common siliciclastic rocks) sedimentary rock. Limestones are rocks that are composed of mostly calcium carbonate (minerals calcite or aragonite).

value.name: Limestone: Rock Uses, Formation, Composition, Pictures - Geology
value.snippet: Limestone is a sedimentary rock composed primarily of calcite, a calcium carbonate mineral with a chemical composition of CaCO 3. It usually forms in clear, calm, warm, shallow marine waters. Limestone is usually a biological sedimentary rock, forming from the accumulation of shell, coral, algal, fecal, and other organic debris.

value.name: Limestone: The Calcium Carbonate Chemical Sedimentary Rock - Geology
value.snippet: "Limestone" means any rock formed mostly of calcium carbonate (CaCO 3), but to geologists, limestone is only one of several types of "carbonate rocks." These rocks are composed of more than 50% carbonate minerals, generally the minerals calcite (pure CaCO 3 ) or dolomite (calcium-magnesium carbonate, CaMg[CO 3 ] 2 ) or both.

value.name: List of types of limestone - Wikipedia
value.snippet: This section is a list of generic types of limestone. Bituminous limestone. Carboniferous Limestone – Limestone deposited during the Dinantian Epoch of the Carboniferous Period. Coquina – Sedimentary rock that is composed mostly of fragments of shells. Coral rag – rubbly limestone composed of ancient coral reef material.

value.name: Limestone - OSRS Wiki
value.snippet: Limestone is also used in Construction. It is a material used for building limestone fireplaces in the Parlour and Dining Room, limestone attack stones in Games Room, stairs in both Quest and Skill halls and imp statues in the Garden. Limestone can also be purchased from Razmire Keelgan's builders store in Mort'ton for 10 coins.
